OUTTAKES: THE RICH GET RICHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jeff Kaye 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Forbes magazine's annual list of the 400 richest Americans may be headed for an 
annual TV special -- with none other than high profile publisher Malcolm Forbes 
hosting. 
</P>
<P>
The Guber-Peters Entertainment Co. -- a division of Columbia Pictures -- is 
putting together the project. Style and format are undecided, but the two-hour 
special would focus on the biggest names on the Forbes 400 list, airing with 
the list's publication, usually October. 
</P>
<P>
But: "We're not in business yet," says Jeff Wald, president of TV for 
Guber-Peters. "We're negotiating." Jeff Kaye 
</P>
