<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLE'S LATINO APPEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you to Quincy Jones for his Feb. 11 remembrance of Nat King Cole on the 
25th anniversary of his untimely death. 
</P>
<P>
Perhaps because of lack of space, while mentioning Cole's successful tours he 
missed the ones to Mexico, South America and Cuba, where he was extremely 
popular. He recorded in Spanish and Portuguese many still-popular favorites. "A 
mis Amigos" (To My Friends), "Cole Espanol" and "More Cole Espanol" are still 
best sellers. 
</P>
<P>
He sang at the opening of Rio's opera house. Wherever he sang the crowds went 
wild. He was the best ambassador the U.S.A. ever had in Latin America. His 
style, in any language, had a universal appeal. 
</P>
<P>
JOSE MANUEL CUETO, MD 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
</TEXT>
