<HEADLINE>
<P>
NORDSTROM 'GUILTY' OF REWARDING INITIATIVE, BUT OTHERS ALSO REQUIRE WORK 'OFF 
THE CLOCK' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shame on Nordstrom for telling its sales associates to pursue their 
entrepreneurial instincts and act as if they actually owned the business ("The 
Other Nordstrom," Feb. 4)! Shame on Nordstrom for honoring those who thrive in 
such an environment by giving them the opportunity to sell more and earn more, 
to avail themselves of enviable merchandise discounts and to aspire to 
increased responsibilities thanks to a strictly enforced promote-from-within 
policy! And shame on Nordstrom for fostering middle management autonomy! 
</P>
<P>
Guilty, I say. 
</P>
<P>
As fitting punishment, let's demand that Nordstrom eliminate the title sales 
associate and replace it with sales clerk. This way we can all hire nothing but 
C-minus people and pay them uniformly for every hour worked. Besides, how else 
can we ensure that Nordstrom will fall into line with the rest of the herd 
leading us to the promised land where mediocrity forever reigns supreme? 
</P>
<P>
HARRY STEVENSON 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 
</P>
</TEXT>
