A comment and an observation: 
</P>
<P>
The idea that enmity between believers in the religions of the Book is a cause 
of Azerbaijani/Armenian fighting has the ring of probable truth. 
</P>
<P>
But I think we must go much further back in time to tap that spring. Of course, 
it is understandable that both East and West will use whatever sticks are 
available. Kipling was on to something. 
</P>
<P>
I smiled when I noticed that the camera had picked up the edge of your 
paste-up, making the words "Azerbaijani attacks against Jews" look as though 
underlined. At least in my copy. 
