<P>
PAPER RECYCLING IN NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Most all Newport residents put out their old newspapers regularly for city 
collection and recycling. All proceeds go to the city. 
</P>
<P>
If the city would dedicate the profits realized from that collection to the 
purchase of different colored trash bags and distribute them free to all 
residents for the separation of waste glass, aluminum and tin cans, Newport 
Beach would find the residents putting out twice the amount of paper and 
cooperating fully with environmental aims and goals -- all with larger net cash 
returns to the city treasury. 
</P>
<P>
HENRY BURKE 
</P>
<P>
Newport Beach 
