<HEADLINE>
<P>
AN EARLY CAMPAIGN OF CURTIS RECALLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have watched, with much bemusement, the current trials and tribulations of 
Mission Viejo Council Member Bob Curtis and the recall election instigated by 
the so-called "Alliance For Mission Viejo." It brought me back to my high 
school days when I helped Bob in his first campaign for a seat on the student 
council. 
</P>
<P>
He hasn't changed all that much. 
</P>
<P>
I have to agree with his critics that Bob can be rude, arrogant and quite 
adamant in his convictions. So what? History has shown us that many of our 
leaders have behaved similarly. It is kind of scary to think that some 
self-serving companies, corporations and individuals are so scared of Bob 
opening his mouth that almost $440,000 has been spent to silence him. 
</P>
<P>
