<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHATSWORTH GIRLS WIN 2ND CITY SOCCER TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE GLAZE, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sooner or later, someone might devise a way to stop the Chatsworth High girls' 
soccer team. 
</P>
<P>
For the second year in a row, the Chancellors plowed through Valley League and 
playoff opponents and, with a 3-0 victory over Palisades at Birmingham High on 
Saturday, placed another City Section championship trophy on their shelf. 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth first-year Coach Bob Horn has visions of a three-peat because all of 
his players will return next year. 
</P>
<P>
"We were stronger this year than last year, and we're going to be stronger next 
year than this year," Horn said. "I don't want to sound cocky, but we have a 
lot of weapons." 
</P>
<P>
Forward Kris Bassler and defender Kim Constantino shared the tournament MVP 
award. Horn suggested that midfielder Heather Gorman, who scored on a breakaway 
at the 17-minute mark in the first half to give the Chancellors a 1-0 lead, 
also should have shared in the award. 
</P>
<P>
One minute after Gorman's goal, a Palisades defensive error helped Bassler 
score a goal that pushed Chatsworth's lead to 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
"We played a 4-4-2 defense trying to control the middle," Dolphin Coach Rick 
Horner said. "Our sweeper tried to come up and let (Bassler) have a one-on-one 
with our goalkeeper." 
</P>
<P>
With three minutes remaining, Constantino scored into an open goal from 20 
yards after a collision between Chatsworth's Sarah Murphy and Dolphin 
goalkeeper Amber Wuchitech sent the ball bouncing into the right flank. 
Wuchitech left the match sporting a black eye. 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth (15-1-1), the Valley League champion, thumped Belmont, 14-0, and 
edged City League champion San Pedro, 4-2, in the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
"I was thinking they might have underestimated us, but they didn't," Horner 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The Dolphins (11-3-1), who outscored their opponents, 57-11, this season, upset 
El Camino Real, 2-1, and 1989 City runner-up Grant, 1-0, en route to the final. 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth crunched Palisades, 10-0, in a first-round playoff match a year ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
