<P>
RANCHO ALAMITOS ROLLS PAST SAN DIMAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rancho Alamitos girls' basketball team advanced further than any other in 
the high school's history, reaching the 3-A final with a 76-50 semifinal 
victory over San Dimas Saturday night at Bolsa Grande High School. 
</P>
<P>
Although the Vaqueros took a 17-0 lead to start the game, San Dimas fought back 
behind forward Natalie Kramer (17 points) to pull within 39-38 at the half. 
</P>
<P>
But San Dimas went cold in the second half, managing only 12 points and 
six-for-35 (17%) shooting. And a minute into the fourth quarter, Kramer fouled 
out. 
</P>
<P>
The Vaqueros were hot outside, making 12 three-point baskets, with Shellie 
Tsuji (18 points) and Melinda Lira (15 points) hitting five each. 
</P>
<P>
"My two guards had their best games of the season tonight, but it was also a 
total team effort tonight," Rancho Alamitos Coach Bob Becker said. 
</P>
<P>
Forward Jenny Newsome had 11 points and 11 rebounds in the third period to 
spark Rancho Alamitos to a 58-46 lead at quarter's end. She finished with a 
team-high 19 points and 14 rebounds. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
