<HEADLINE>
<P>
EL CAMINO REAL EASY WINNER IN CITY SECTION WRESTLING FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David Aparicio, Greg McMurray, Roy Steinbock and Saul Emard posted victories to 
lift El Camino Real High to the City Section wrestling championship Saturday at 
Granada Hills High. 
</P>
<P>
The Conquistadores finished with 190 points to outdistance Canoga Park (157 
1/2), Fremont (142), San Fernando (88 1/2) and Granada Hills (79). 
</P>
<P>
McMurray, named the meet's outstanding wrestler, pinned Hector Cervantes of 
Fremont in 4 minutes 43 seconds. McMurray, a senior, finished fifth meet in the 
state last year. 
</P>
<P>
Other Valley winners included Canoga Park's Mario Acosta (98 pounds), Steve 
Pratt (126) and Chris Camarena (132); San Fernando's Greg Tan (154); Granada 
Hills' Karl Finley (175); Birmingham's Barak Isaacs (191); and Chatsworth's 
Raymundo Martinez (245). 
</P>
<P>
The winners in each category advance to the state meet Friday and Saturday in 
Stockton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
