<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
East German Gabi Kohlisch, in her final race, won the women's singles event at 
the 27th World Luge Championships at Calgary. 
</P>
<P>
Kohlisch, 26, navigated down the 1,050-meter track at Canada Olympic Park in a 
combined time of 1 minute 32.553 seconds in two runs to edge Julia Antipova of 
the Soviet Union and West Germany's Jana Bode. 
</P>
<P>
Kohlisch's trainer, Franz Schneider, died two weeks ago after suffering a heart 
attack in his car and crashing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
