<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 4; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
130 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Darryl Usher, a reserve wide receiver and kick returner for the San Diego 
Chargers and Phoenix Cardinals last season, was shot to death at his apartment 
in Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
Police said a man entered Usher's apartment and shot and killed Usher and 
Chiquita Burt, 24, believed to be Usher's girlfriend. 
</P>
<P>
The attacker, who was not identified, is in critical condition after apparently 
turning the gun on himself. He is believed to have been a former boyfriend of 
Burt. 
</P>
<P>
The 5-foot-8, 170-pound Usher was signed as a free agent by the Cardinals last 
November after being released by the Chargers. He was not protected by the 
Cardinals Feb. 1 and became an unconditional free agent. 
</P>
<P>
Usher, a second-year pro out of Illinois, was drafted in 1988 in seventh-round 
by the Patriots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
