<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW MEXICO STATE ROLLS OVER SAN JOSE FOR 16-0 HOME MARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS CRUCES, N.M. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Keith Hill scored 22 points and Randy Brown had 21, including eight in a row 
late in the first half, as No. 24 New Mexico State beat San Jose State, 101-70, 
Saturday night and finished the year 16-0 at home. 
</P>
<P>
The Aggies (23-3, 14-2 in the Big West) have two road games and the conference 
tournament left. 
</P>
<P>
Brown's eight points sparked a 14-3 run. He scored on a three-point shot, a 
three-point play and then stole the ball and scored on a dunk to give the 
Aggies a 37-27 lead. 
</P>
<P>
San Jose State (7-18, 4-11), which rallied from deficits of 10-0 and 21-13, 
never recovered. New Mexico State led at halftime, 47-35. 
</P>
<P>
Michael New and Reggie Jordan added 18 points apiece for New Mexico State, 
which broke the 100-point mark for the second game in a row and for the fourth 
time this season. Kenne Young led the Spartans with 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
