<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRE CAUSES POWER OUTAGE IN DOWNTOWN SEATTLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEATTLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 70 blocks of downtown Seattle lost electrical power for several hours 
Saturday after a fire in a transformer vault. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported. 
</P>
<P>
The outage darkened hotel lobbies and shut down switching equipment for the 
Washington State Lottery, leaving many people unable to buy tickets on the 
night of a $6-million drawing, one of the state's largest. 
</P>
<P>
The area of the power outage encompassed Pike Place Market, several major 
department stores, the Seattle Aquarium and the Port of Seattle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
FIRES -- WASHINGTON (STATE); SEATTLE (WA); POWER FAILURES 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
