<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 WOMEN WALKING ON SIDEWALK HIT AND KILLED BY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LUZ VILLARREAL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two elderly women were killed Saturday when a car struck them as they were 
walking on a sidewalk on the 2500 block of West Broadway, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the car, Denise Arlene Perreira, 22, Anaheim, was arrested on 
suspicion of manslaughter and driving under the influence of drugs, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
One of the victims was pronounced dead at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
The other died at Humana Hospital-West Anaheim, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The names of the victims were not released pending notification of their 
families. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Perreira was driving east on Broadway about noon when her car 
veered across the street, struck the two women on the sidewalk, then crashed 
into a tree. 
</P>
<P>
Perreira was taken to Anaheim Memorial Hospital for injuries she received in 
the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
