<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROBBER TAKES $1,200 AT BEACH BLVD. BANK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police are searching for a woman who robbed a branch of the Union Bank on 
Friday and escaped with $1,200 in cash. 
</P>
<P>
The robbery occurred shortly after noon, when the woman entered the bank on the 
17000 block of Beach Boulevard and demanded money from a teller at gunpoint, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
The teller handed over $1,200, and the robber fled. She was seen getting into a 
tan Ford sedan driven by a man. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the robber was 24 to 30 years old, about 5 feet, 3 inches tall and 
weighed about 145 pounds. She had long brown hair and was wearing a dark blue 
shirt and pants, police said. 
</P>
