<HEADLINE>
<P>
SMALL-SCREEN CINEMA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN THOMAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The Fourth Protocol" (KCOP, Monday at 8 p.m. and again on Saturday at 8 p.m.) 
is a misfired 1987 spy thriller, laying waste to Michael Caine, Pierce Brosnan, 
Joanna Cassidy and others. 
</P>
<P>
"The Last Dragon" (KTLA, Tuesday at 8 p.m.) is a ludicrous but entertaining 
1985 martial arts movie starring Taimak as a black Bruce Lee. 
</P>
<P>
"Hot Dog: The Movie" (KTLA, Thursday a 8 p.m.) offers a great young cast and 
dazzling Squaw Valley locales, but the 1984 film about a world skiing 
competition is spoiled by calculated raunchy sex scenes and a noticeable racist 
tone. KEVIN THOMAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA022590-0227 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 182433 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 25, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
